{
  "article_id": "NewYorkDailyTribune1893",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Colonel J. Colton Lynes",
        "entity_key": "ccly",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Agricultural College of South Georgia",
        "entity_key": "in_asg",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who is now seeking to obtain some consular or diplomatic appointment, has already had considerable experience abroad as translator and bookkeeper of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "United States Legation",
        "entity_key": "gov_usleg",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Paris",
        "entity_key": "ci_paris",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". All the correspondence between "
      },
      {
        "text": "Bismarck",
        "entity_key": "bismarck",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Washburne",
        "entity_key": "washburne",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Thiers",
        "entity_key": "thiers",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was translated by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Colonel Lynes",
        "entity_key": "ccly",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and transcribed into a volume now in the archives in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Washington",
        "entity_key": "ci_dc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mr. Van Leer Polk",
        "entity_key": "vlp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nashville, Tenn.",
        "entity_key": "ci_nash",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who will soon sail for "
      },
      {
        "text": "Calcutta",
        "entity_key": "ci_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where he will represent the "
      },
      {
        "text": "United States Government",
        "entity_key": "gov_usa",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "as Consul-General, says that he means to give up his home style of dress and drink, and to live like the natives. He thinks this is the secret of escaping cholera and other diseases in foreign lands."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Carl Luther",
        "entity_key": "cluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a counsellor in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "German Ministry of Labor",
        "entity_key": "gov_gml",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who died a few days ago in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Schoenebeck",
        "entity_key": "ci_scho",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Germany",
        "entity_key": "co_ger",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was a direct descendant of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Jacob Luther",
        "entity_key": "jluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the youngest brother of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Martin Luther",
        "entity_key": "mluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". His father, "
      },
      {
        "text": "August Christian Valentin Gottleib Luther",
        "entity_key": "aluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", bore a striking resemblance to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the great leader of the Reformation",
        "entity_key": "mluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Germany",
        "entity_key": "co_ger",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". A "
      },
      {
        "text": "young brother",
        "entity_key": "luthbrother",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the dead man",
        "entity_key": "cluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was killed in the battle of "
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Privat",
        "entity_key": "ci_privat",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Direct descendants of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Martin Luther",
        "entity_key": "mluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", through his son, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Paul Luther",
        "entity_key": "pluth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", body physician of the Elector of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Saxony",
        "entity_key": "ci_sax",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", still live in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Germany",
        "entity_key": "co_ger",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Among them is "
      },
      {
        "text": "Deacon Paul Luther",
        "entity_key": "pluth1",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Kremmen",
        "entity_key": "ci_krem",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The family in each generation has usually had several members in the church. A number of the female descendants of the reformer have married into the families of the nobility."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rev. D. F. Bradley",
        "entity_key": "dfb",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", pastor of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Park Congregational Church",
        "entity_key": "ch_pcc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Grand Rapids, Mich.",
        "entity_key": "ci_gr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was born at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Bangkok, Siam",
        "entity_key": "ci_bk",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in 1857, of missionary parents. He remained in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Siam",
        "entity_key": "co_th",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "until 1877, acquiring among other things, a knowledge of the Siamese language. He is a graduate of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Oberlin College",
        "entity_key": "in_obc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ohio",
        "entity_key": "st_oh",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The Virginia press",
        "entity_key": "vap",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "is urgently recommending the appointment of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Senator John W. Daniel",
        "entity_key": "jwd",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "that State",
        "entity_key": "st_va",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to succeed "
      },
      {
        "text": "Justice Blatchford",
        "entity_key": "blatch",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "on the Supreme Bench. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Senator Daniel",
        "entity_key": "jwd",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "is a close friend of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Senator David B. Hill",
        "entity_key": "dbh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and an ardent advocate of free coinage, neither of which qualifications is likely to be of much weight with "
      },
      {
        "text": "President Cleveland",
        "entity_key": "gcl",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Captain Oscar G. Lenge",
        "entity_key": "ogl",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who has just died at his home in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Chicago",
        "entity_key": "ci_chic",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was the first Swede to settle in "
      },
      {
        "text": "that city",
        "entity_key": "ci_chic",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He also, in 1838, opened the first drug store anywhere in that neighborhood. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Lenge",
        "entity_key": "ogl",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "obtained his title from his marine experience. He was for a period connected with the "
      },
      {
        "text": "United States",
        "entity_key": "mi_navy",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "English navies",
        "entity_key": "mi_engnavy",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and subsequently was engaged in the merchant marine service just previous to his coming to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Chicago",
        "entity_key": "ci_chic",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Captain Milton T. Russel",
        "entity_key": "mtl",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Des Moines, Iowa",
        "entity_key": "ci_dm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", has just published the reminiscences of his prison life in and escape from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Libby Prison",
        "entity_key": "libby",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "during the war. He was captain of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Company A, Fifty-first Indiana Infantry",
        "entity_key": "mi_51ia",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and was captured with Colonel Streight's command, near "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome, Ga.",
        "entity_key": "ci_rga",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", during that fearless and famous raid into the heart of the Southern Confederacy."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A recent earthquake at ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas Island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", near ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara, Cal.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", has revived interest in the story of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the old Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who led a Crusoe life on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for many years.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She was left there by accident in 1836, and her existence forgotten until twenty years later, when "
      },
      {
        "text": "a Santa Barbara hunter",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for otters, found her there and brought her to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "She had entirely forgotten her language, and in consequence the story of her hermitage was never known.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Three months after her rescue she died, and was buried by the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mr. Henry O'Meara",
        "entity_key": "meara",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Boston",
        "entity_key": "ci_bo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who was the poet at the recent dedication of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Farragut",
        "entity_key": "farragut",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "statue in "
      },
      {
        "text": "that city",
        "entity_key": "ci_bo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", has been invited to contribute a hymn for the parliament of religions to be held at the World's Fair."
      }
    ]
  ]
}